lines.text: You should have listened to Doug!
Looking for a cop?
It can't be!
But it is!!!

According to psychiatric records, Henley - Vickers - came from a broken home, abused child. Police were always being called in to break up fights. State finally got custody of him during his formative years. It was then that Henley came to believe God was on his side and would always take care of him. Then when the state kicked him out on the street, Henley came to believe that God had deserted him. And that's when he turned to Satan.
You have the right to remain...*dead*.
Sarah, now stop this, you're obstructing justice. Ha ha ha.
Oh God!
God? Hah! God has nothing to do with it! If you know what I mean.
Let's take the tape player and go off into the woods?
No WAY, Eric! There's too many MOSQUITOES!
Where were you?
I went over to the caretakers to get that stupid jacuzzi started but the guy's disappeared
What do you MEAN he's disappeared?
I'm mean I looked ALL over his place and I couldn't find the guy.
A couple hours ago, I thought I heard someone screaming. Sounded like it was coming from the woods.
No one ELSE heard it, Doug
But what if was the caretaker. You just said the guy disappeared
Just because a guy is NOT around doesn't mean something HAPPENED to him.
But what if it HAD, Zach?
